## NET-NEW Findings This Session (C144 Phase 03)
1. **CSRD Phase 2 double materiality assessment deadline June 2026** — 60%+ of large entities not yet started. DMA methodology gap significant. Advisory opportunity: DMA workshop facilitation + documentation + auditor-ready file preparation. Geneva-based multinationals with EU subsidiaries particularly exposed.
2. **DORA TPRM US hyperscaler dependency advisory** — DORA Art. 5-6 third-party ICT risk. Swiss financial institutions with AWS/Azure/GCP EU-connected infrastructure need DORA-compliant exit planning. Workaround frameworks being explored. ICT TPRM gap assessment + exit scenario advisory.
3. **Geneva corporate tax reform STAF II/PTP cantonal implementation** — Federal Tax Court 2C_480/2023 precedent creating intercantonal tax allocation disputes. Geneva cantonal tax increase 2026 adding complexity. Multi-cantonal restructuring advisory demand from Geneva-headquartered groups.
4. **NOVE energy efficiency ordinance Geneva SME advisory window** — Energy audits required for large enterprises. Cantonal reporting obligations. Renewable energy procurement advisory. Geneva SMEs with manufacturing or real estate operations most affected.
5. **Swiss precision manufacturing nearshoring FDI advisory** — US tariff-driven reshoring creating Swiss precision manufacturing nearshoring candidate demand. SECO FDI screening creates 30-60 day review period. Nearshoring feasibility study + regulatory mapping advisory.
6. **Geneva fractional CFO CSRD/DORA/ESG premium widening** — CHF 2,500-3,500/day for specialized mandates. Board accountability driving demand. SME/mid-market Geneva companies unable to hire full-time specialists. Fractional engagement model: 2-5 days/month on retainer.

